<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="441" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Dupuy de Lôme</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-20"><hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 33.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge your
                            telegram of the 19th instant, and to say that copies of the same have
                            been communicated to the Departments of Justice and of the Treasury with
                            the request for such immediate official action as will tend to prevent
                            any violation of the neutrality laws of the United States or to punish
                            any such violations as actually occur.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>